This article summarizes an executive order issued by President Joe Biden regarding criminal justice reform. The order emphasizes the need for fair and impartial justice, community-oriented policing, and accountability for law enforcement misconduct. It acknowledges the impact of systemic racism on the criminal justice system and calls for the elimination of racial disparities. The order also addresses issues such as officer recruitment, training, and wellness, as well as the use of force, body-worn cameras, and advanced law enforcement technologies. It promotes alternatives to arrest and incarceration, reentry support, and comprehensive data collection. The order aims to strengthen relationships between law enforcement and communities, improve conditions in prisons and jails, and support safe and effective policing through grantmaking. The executive order revokes previous orders that are inconsistent with its provisions.